This article is a transcript of President Trump's remarks during the Coast Guard Academy graduation ceremony. He expressed his gratitude and appreciation for the Coast Guard and their service to the country. He also highlighted their dedication to public service and their involvement in community service activities. President Trump discussed the importance of the Coast Guard in protecting America's borders, combating drug trafficking and human trafficking, and securing the nation's waters. He praised their skills and bravery in performing their duties and assured them of his support as their Commander-in-Chief. The President also mentioned his upcoming trip abroad and his commitment to promoting peace and security. He concluded by thanking and congratulating the Coast Guard Class of 2017.